name: Michelle Mao
details: Graduating senior that spends most of her time on the student-teaching community at Cal. I love this community because in a self-selecting fashion it has gathered the most kind, selfless, and wholehearted people I've met in my four years here. When I'm not on campus (or for this semester in my apt) you can find me biking around Berkeley or snowboarding in Tahoe.

name: Katherine Shu
details: Hi! I’m a third year EECS Major from around LA. I enjoy traveling, dancing, and drawing. Against popular belief, I don’t like chocolate and I drink boba with no sugar and no ice. I hope you all have an amazing semester!! :)

name: Brian Lee
details: Hi everyone - I am Brian, a 5th Year MS student! I tend to drink an unhealthy amount of Coke Zero, but I am trying to lose weight, so if you catch me drinking it, remind me to stop (please)! I look forward to a great semester with all of you!

name: Richard Roggenkemper
details: Hi! My name is Richard. I'm a third year student from Los Gatos, California. I’m a Computer Science/Data Science major. I love skiing, cooking, and anything related to food. I’m excited to be Communications Chair and a CS 61a SAM this semester!

name: Albert Tang
details: I'd like to think of myself as the Kawhi Leonard of CSM - I'm a fun guy. I am here to make sure that all of you enjoy your virtual semester in CSM :)

name: Jade Singh
details: Hi, I'm Jade and I'm a senior studying CS and music!  When I'm not doing 61A related things, you can find me eating Chipotle or watching Disney movies, or maybe even eating Chipotle while watching Disney movies.  I'm also a TA for 61A and this is my sixth time teaching the class, so ask me anything about 61A :)

name: Jason Chang
details: Hiya, my name is Jason! I'm a fourth-year majoring in Computer Science and Applied Math, and this is my 5th semester with CSM. On the rare occasions when I'm not putting my nose to the grindstone, I really enjoy cooking, listening to Korean music I can only half-understand, and daydreaming about the useless things on my Amazon wishlist.

name: Samantha Adams
details: Hi there! I'm a graduating senior in EECS and this is my third semester teaching CS 61B. In my free time (lol what's that), I really enjoy hiking, playing video games, and sleeping in. I also drink way too much chai and I've slowly been teaching myself how to play guitar. I really love this class and can't wait to share that love with you!

name: Ryan Nuqui
details: Hi all, my name is Ryan and I'm a fourth year CS and Applied Math major with a minor in Data Science. I'm super excited to be teaching CS 61B again since it's my favorite class to teach (and I hope you'll be able to enjoy it just as much)! I'm very fond of playing board games, trying my best at badminton, and ducks (feel free to ask me for a rubber duck). Looking forward to a great semester :))

name: Shreya Kannan
details: Hiya everyone, I'm super excited to be with CSM and CS 88 for a fourth semester now! A little about me: I prefer musicals over concerts, cold over warm weather, dancing over singing, and sushi over tacos. I'd love to meet you all, so don't hesitate to reach out!

name: Sohum Hulyalkar
details: hi! how's life? hopefully life is going well! if its not, smile and it'll be a bit better :)

name: Mohsin Sarwari
details: Hi! I'm a third year CS and Stats Major. I love playing squash (the sport, not the vegetable). I am skilled at ruining family photos and dropping contact lenses. I am passionate about teaching and keen on getting better.

name: Dylan Brater
details: Hi everyone, I'm a third year EECS major and this is my third semester in CSM. My favorite Berkeley restaurant is Thai basil, but I'm currently living in my home town of San Diego. My favorite hobby over quarantine has been rewatching a lot of shows that I loved when I was younger.

name: Naomi Sagan
details: Hi! I'm Naomi, and I'm excited to be your 16B co-coordinator this semester!  In my spare time, I enjoy running, playing flute and cooking. I've been part of CSM 16B since it was first introduced a year ago, and I want to help make this the best semester of CSM 16B yet!
